post_text: We are so proud of the class of 2020! Good luck to all of these students.
shared_text:
Nebraska City High School
May 10 at 10:21 PM ·

May 10th, 2020 turned out to be a special day for our Seniors thanks to the community of Nebraska City. So many people lined the streets to cheer and applaud the efforts of the Class of 2020. A special thank you to: Fernando Dominguez and B-103 for delivering messages and a great playlist, the NCPD and NC Fire & Rescue for their time and assistance, the NC City Council, and all the volunteers who dedicated their time to ensuring this was a special day. IT IS A GREAT DAY TO BE A PIONEER!

shared_text:
Nebraska City News-Press
April 22 at 4:37 PM ·

Members of the Class of 2020 from Lourdes Central Catholic, NCECBVI, and Nebraska City High School are scheduled to receive yard signs celebrating their graduation, courtesy of the Nebraska City Community Foundation Fund.The NCCFF hope the yard signs will help the graduates celebrate this huge accomplishment.

Signs will be distributed from 4 to 6 p.m. today (April 22) at the South Shelter in Steinhart Park.

Graduates were instructed to enter the park at the North entrance by the Aquatic Center and drive to the South Shelter where they would be handed a yard sign and a congratulatory letter from the NCCFF.

The students would then exit the park via the South exit by the golf course.

While practicing appropriate social distancing, NCCFF supporters plan to stand along the park drive, waving and shouting encouragement to the graduates.

post_text: NCHS Seniors:
shared_text:
Nebraska City Community Foundation Fund
April 18 at 2:55 PM ·

Attention, All Graduating High School Seniors in Nebraska City!

Your own 2020 high school graduate yard sign has been prepared for you. Here’s how to get yours.
On Wednesday, April 22 from 4 - 6:00 p.m., drive through Steinhart Park, coming in from the North entrance by the Aquatic Center. Drive around the pond to the South side. Several NCCFF supporters will distribute the signs from the South Shelter. We will all practice appropriate social distancing. You don’t even have to get out of your car. A yard sign will be handed to you.
After getting your sign, simply leave the park from the South exit by the golf course.
Congratulations to you all! We are so proud of you. Enjoy your sign, courtesy of the Nebraska City Community Foundation Fund.

post_text: Come support our seniors at 8:20 tonight!
shared_text:
Nebraska City High School
April 15 at 4:33 PM ·

Nebraska City and Lourdes Central Catholic will be honoring our 2020 seniors as well as all of our athletes who would be participating in this year's spring sports. A beacon of light ceremony is scheduled for Wednesday, April 15th, at 8:20 PM to support all students who have been impacted by their school's closure. Schools from across the state of Nebraska will be participating in this ceremony. Supporters can participate by turning on their outside lights at their homes from 8:20 to 8:40 PM. NCHS and LCC will participate by turning on the lights at Pioneer Stadium for 20 minutes beginning at 8:20 PM. Please follow the CDC guidelines for social distancing. Residents or students should not gather at the stadium but are welcome to drive by.
